1
00:00:39,070 --> 00:00:40,670
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,670 --> 00:00:42,080
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:45,980
No way! This can't be happening!

4
00:00:47,080 --> 00:00:48,080
What's wrong, Mr. Ha?

5
00:00:53,890 --> 00:00:55,120
(Update 2: "Momo's mother, Hyun Ran Hee,
Suspected in Apparent Suicide")

6
00:00:58,090 --> 00:00:59,330
That's Geum Ba Ra for you.

7
00:00:59,330 --> 00:01:01,360
She's first on scene and gets top intel.
She's our rookie, too.

8
00:01:01,430 --> 00:01:02,960
What is going on?

9
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:05,130
The secret engagement story just blew up.

10
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:08,530
Gosh, someone's dying every day now.

11
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:09,600
The third update is out.

12
00:01:12,270 --> 00:01:13,270
Hurry up!

13
00:01:27,750 --> 00:01:29,820
Ma'am, it's dangerous.
Come on, what are you doing?

14
00:01:30,790 --> 00:01:33,860
- Gosh, Chief!
- You're relentless. Seriously.

15
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:51,580
(Unpo Police Station)

16
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:03,360
Excuse me.

17
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:06,630
Do you have someone to help
around the house?

18
00:02:07,930 --> 00:02:09,760
Who does the cleaning...

19
00:02:11,230 --> 00:02:13,530
Was it just you and your mother
living here?

20
00:02:19,770 --> 00:02:22,140
Shouldn't you have rushed her
to the hospital?

21
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:24,680
You didn't even perform CPR.

22
00:02:25,810 --> 00:02:27,810
It was too late for CPR.

23
00:02:28,380 --> 00:02:30,450
You just end up breaking their ribs
at that point.

24
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,860
- Should we move her?
- Yes.

25
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:43,460
Mom!

26
00:02:45,930 --> 00:02:47,230
- We're going in.
- You can't enter.

27
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,630
We're close to her in both work and life.

28
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:50,500
- If we can't go in, who can?
- Let us go in.

29
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,240
We're practically family.

30
00:02:53,310 --> 00:02:55,440
- Who's in charge here?
- The police!

31
00:02:56,610 --> 00:02:57,840
Just give us one comment!

32
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,110
- Hey, let us through.
- Yes. sir.

33
00:03:02,980 --> 00:03:04,280
- Is that confirmed, Chief?
- Look over here!

34
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:05,350
- Make way!
- Step back!

35
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:21,700
It's me.

36
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,510
Are we sure it's a suicide?

37
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:28,310
- Yes.
- Cause of death?

38
00:03:28,370 --> 00:03:30,740
- Hypothermia, most likely.
- Hypothermia?

39
00:03:30,810 --> 00:03:32,350
The bedroom's an absolute freezer.

40
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:33,610
The AC was...

41
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:38,650
This is not the time or place!

42
00:04:09,580 --> 00:04:10,580
They're coming out!

43
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:33,810
Momo.

44
00:04:55,490 --> 00:04:56,500
Hello.

45
00:04:58,100 --> 00:05:00,900
You must be Momo's mother,
CEO Hyun Ran Hee.

46
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,480
Ba Ra.

47
00:05:13,050 --> 00:05:14,910
- You actually came.
- Of course.

48
00:05:15,180 --> 00:05:16,320
Your mother is here too.

49
00:05:16,780 --> 00:05:17,780
Goodness.

50
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:20,990
Ms. Hyun.

51
00:05:21,690 --> 00:05:23,220
I didn't expect to see you here.

52
00:05:23,820 --> 00:05:24,920
Neither did I.

53
00:05:25,420 --> 00:05:26,430
What brings you here?

54
00:05:26,690 --> 00:05:28,290
This is Geum Ba Ra,
a reporter from Sungwoo Daily.

55
00:05:29,530 --> 00:05:31,330
- Hello.
- Hello.

56
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:35,030
She's covering the exhibition today,
and my schedule just happened to be free.

57
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:39,240
Are you close with CEO Ju Yeong Ae?

58
00:05:40,170 --> 00:05:42,710
No. My senior editor sent me to cover it.

59
00:05:42,910 --> 00:05:44,710
Mom, do you have an exhibition coming up?

60
00:05:44,710 --> 00:05:45,810
It's in the works.

61
00:05:46,110 --> 00:05:47,510
- That's Momo, right?
- Yes.

62
00:05:47,910 --> 00:05:49,450
She's so much prettier in person.

63
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:51,480
I'll be back.

64
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:56,920
Look at CEO Ju, schmoozing.

65
00:06:11,740 --> 00:06:14,270
You can't just disappear on me
like last time.

66
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:16,540
Chairman Kang has arrived.

67
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:17,640
- Welcome.
- It's my pleasure.

68
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:20,010
Excuse me for a moment.

69
00:06:25,820 --> 00:06:26,820
Hello.

70
00:06:29,290 --> 00:06:30,560
This is my daughter.

71
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:33,360
Artist Paul Kim. He was based in Germany.

72
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:34,960
It's a pleasure to meet you.

73
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:37,060
Hello.

74
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:40,200
Your pieces have already sold, you know.
Both of them.

75
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:45,400
She's a close reporter friend of mine
from Sungwoo Daily.

76
00:06:48,010 --> 00:06:50,940
- Excuse me. Is Artist Paul Kim here?
- Yes.

77
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:54,280
- That's him.
- How's your work coming along?

78
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:55,680
It's been a little slow lately.

79
00:06:56,380 --> 00:06:58,680
What do you do to relax?
Besides photography trips?

80
00:06:59,350 --> 00:07:00,990
I just read books and whatnot.

81
00:07:02,990 --> 00:07:04,390
Korea's changed a lot, hasn't it?

82
00:07:05,390 --> 00:07:07,390
Have you been back much?

83
00:07:07,730 --> 00:07:08,760
No.

84
00:07:09,630 --> 00:07:10,700
She doesn't look like you.

85
00:07:13,330 --> 00:07:15,070
An improvement on the original, right?

86
00:07:15,530 --> 00:07:18,070
I've never met her,
but I'm told I look like my grandmother.

87
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:22,640
Excuse me, could I get a picture?

88
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,010
Thank you.

89
00:07:28,210 --> 00:07:30,080
Give me a call next time you're in Seoul.

90
00:07:30,420 --> 00:07:31,580
You must be busy, though.

91
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:33,420
It's fine as long as it's not last-minute.

92
00:07:35,890 --> 00:07:37,160
This is Artist Paul Kim.

93
00:07:38,690 --> 00:07:41,630
Hello. I'm Geum Ba Ra
from the Culture Desk at Sungwoo Daily.

94
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:45,930
- Hi. I don't have a card yet.
- Please.

95
00:07:45,930 --> 00:07:47,800
Your work is your business card.

96
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:52,440
Would you mind telling me a little
about your piece?

97
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:58,610
Let me just get a picture first.

98
00:07:58,980 --> 00:08:00,780
I'm not planning to run the story
right away.

99
00:08:05,780 --> 00:08:07,920
You'll get fans after this photo gets out,
won't you?

100
00:08:36,920 --> 00:08:37,920
What about the suicide note?

101
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:43,220
- The forensics team has it.
- What does it say?

102
00:08:50,430 --> 00:08:52,600
(Emergency Medical Center)

103
00:09:01,410 --> 00:09:03,140
- What happened?
- It appears to be a suicide.

104
00:09:03,210 --> 00:09:04,210
Okay, right this way.

105
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:55,620
Ma'am, we're going to need you
to come down to the station.

106
00:10:59,830 --> 00:11:03,000
- We'll confirm with handwriting analysis.
- Understood.

107
00:11:03,060 --> 00:11:06,830
Check the gallery office, not the house,
for any documents handwritten by Ms. Hyun.

108
00:11:07,070 --> 00:11:08,100
Got it.

109
00:11:08,700 --> 00:11:10,800
Let me see the suicide note.
I won't write it in the article.

110
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,310
You've already gotten your scoop.

111
00:11:16,940 --> 00:11:17,980
Go in my office.

112
00:11:17,980 --> 00:11:19,410
Reporters will be
swarming in here any minute.

113
00:11:23,350 --> 00:11:26,790
I can't imagine how you're feeling,
but we need to get your statement.

114
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:31,320
Can you walk us through what happened?

115
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,590
What time did you find her?

116
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:36,800
I don't know.

117
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:40,700
I didn't have anything scheduled today,
so I slept in a little.

118
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:45,870
And when I woke up,

119
00:11:48,140 --> 00:11:49,340
it was quiet,

120
00:11:50,580 --> 00:11:52,510
so I figured she had gone to the gallery.

121
00:11:59,990 --> 00:12:02,590
How'd you know to call?
I literally just walked in.

122
00:12:03,660 --> 00:12:04,890
James just told me.

123
00:12:05,490 --> 00:12:06,790
Do you have plans for Christmas Eve?

124
00:12:06,790 --> 00:12:08,290
You know I don't make any special plans.

125
00:12:08,690 --> 00:12:10,900
I always have dinner with you
on Christmas Eve.

126
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,670
We're thicker than blood, I swear.

127
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:15,400
Does just sharing blood make you family?

128
00:12:15,570 --> 00:12:16,570
Exactly.

129
00:12:17,140 --> 00:12:18,740
Because plenty of siblings
are worse than strangers.

130
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:19,970
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

131
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:21,310
You should do a talent donation this time.

132
00:12:22,010 --> 00:12:23,380
What talent do I even have?

133
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:26,380
Perform at the Sponsor Appreciation Night
at Nua Children's Home.

134
00:12:26,380 --> 00:12:27,650
My fingers are stiff now.

135
00:12:27,710 --> 00:12:29,110
They'll loosen up if you practice.

136
00:12:29,780 --> 00:12:31,250
It'd be great if James could come too.

137
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:33,450
(Auditorium)

138
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:34,750
Come on, let's go.

139
00:12:39,830 --> 00:12:42,160
- Hello.
- We keep running into each other.

140
00:12:42,260 --> 00:12:44,600
- It's not over, is it?
- Part two is about to start.

141
00:12:45,530 --> 00:12:48,600
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

142
00:12:53,310 --> 00:12:55,040
- Thank you.
- I'm a huge fan.

143
00:12:59,610 --> 00:13:01,380
- Hello.
- Hello.

144
00:13:01,780 --> 00:13:03,120
Are you enjoying the food?

145
00:13:18,330 --> 00:13:21,330
(Nua General Hospital)

146
00:13:22,530 --> 00:13:24,200
Do you come to this every year?

147
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:25,740
Yes.

148
00:13:28,270 --> 00:13:31,180
The vibe here is so great with the music.

149
00:13:34,780 --> 00:13:36,110
You're drinking quite a bit today.

150
00:13:37,020 --> 00:13:38,050
It's Christmas Eve.

151
00:13:38,850 --> 00:13:40,750
Next year, I'll keep my schedule clear,

152
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:43,060
come early, and have a meal with the kids.

153
00:13:43,590 --> 00:13:44,590
You definitely should.

154
00:13:59,270 --> 00:14:00,670
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

155
00:15:54,290 --> 00:15:55,850
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

156
00:16:23,820 --> 00:16:26,020
(Nua Children's Home)

157
00:16:37,860 --> 00:16:39,160
(Nua Children's Home)

158
00:16:39,230 --> 00:16:40,970
- How'd the surgery go?
- It went well.

159
00:16:40,970 --> 00:16:43,340
The Chairman is on a call
with Ambassador Yu Gu Jong.

160
00:16:43,340 --> 00:16:45,400
All right. Is Momo here yet?

161
00:16:45,540 --> 00:16:47,910
Yes, she's a big hit with our guests.

162
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,410
I'm so jealous.

163
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:56,010
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

164
00:17:03,220 --> 00:17:04,320
You're here.

165
00:17:04,660 --> 00:17:07,030
- Advisor.
- Where's your father?

166
00:17:08,990 --> 00:17:10,860
- Advisor!
- What is it?

167
00:17:10,930 --> 00:17:12,400
- What's going on?
- Advisor!

168
00:17:19,270 --> 00:17:20,740
Are you adopting another one?

169
00:17:23,010 --> 00:17:24,010
No.

170
00:17:25,140 --> 00:17:28,010
- It's not been long since Oiji passed.
- Where are you?

171
00:17:28,780 --> 00:17:29,850
Here.

172
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:36,220
I thought you'd be pulling an all-nighter
with Ju Shin.

173
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:38,420
Momo's sponsored by your company, right?

174
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:40,690
- Yes.
- Introduce me.

175
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:42,560
- Was Momo at the party too?
- Yes.

176
00:17:43,460 --> 00:17:46,500
Forget about it.
She's getting engaged to Ju Shin soon.

177
00:17:48,930 --> 00:17:49,940
Really?

178
00:17:50,340 --> 00:17:51,340
Yes.

179
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:56,810
- Did you introduce them?
- Ju Shin is head over heels for her.

180
00:17:57,210 --> 00:18:00,950
That's why Momo's here.
She'll be the foundation's first lady.

181
00:18:04,180 --> 00:18:06,690
Go have a cold beer to cool off
instead of just water.

182
00:18:08,890 --> 00:18:10,120
How are things between you and Eun Ah?

183
00:18:14,730 --> 00:18:17,400
Of all people, Momo?
I'm on Team Geum Ba Ra.

184
00:18:42,490 --> 00:18:43,490
Hello.

185
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:49,460
It's cold out here.

186
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:51,260
It's too hot inside.

187
00:18:52,660 --> 00:18:55,970
I made a fool of myself the other day.
I didn't know you were Ju Shin's friend.

188
00:18:57,240 --> 00:18:59,910
I got carried away hearing live music
for the first time in a while.

189
00:19:01,810 --> 00:19:02,940
Do you have a side gig?

190
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:05,610
I'm not good enough to moonlight.

191
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,510
I'm so jealous of people
who can play an instrument.

192
00:19:09,150 --> 00:19:11,820
- You could just learn.
- Then you can tutor me part-time.

193
00:19:15,850 --> 00:19:16,960
Where's Ju Shin?

194
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:19,930
- The restroom.
- Is his stomach acting up again?

195
00:19:20,230 --> 00:19:23,160
Yes.
And he only had juice on the way over.

196
00:19:24,260 --> 00:19:25,860
I guess that's
how the skies keep things fair.

197
00:19:25,860 --> 00:19:27,530
Ju Shin has a weak stomach,

198
00:19:28,270 --> 00:19:29,800
but he's an A-plus in every other way.

199
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:34,940
I'm Ha Yong Joong, by the way.

200
00:19:35,310 --> 00:19:39,580
With the Advisor collapsing that day,
Ju Shin never got to introduce us.

201
00:19:41,110 --> 00:19:42,210
I'm Momo.

202
00:19:42,210 --> 00:19:44,850
I looked you up. It's your real name.

203
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:48,020
Yes,
a lot of people assume it's a stage name.

204
00:19:49,860 --> 00:19:51,290
So why did you look me up?

205
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,130
Curious about me as an actress?

206
00:19:57,900 --> 00:19:59,460
Or as your friend's girlfriend?

207
00:20:02,430 --> 00:20:04,370
Both, of course.

208
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:11,010
I hear you've been very busy.

209
00:20:11,340 --> 00:20:14,250
I was away for a while,
so I have a lot to catch up on.

210
00:20:14,450 --> 00:20:17,520
Everyone's been swamped.
Especially Ju Shin, of course.

211
00:20:19,420 --> 00:20:20,490
Ju Shin...

212
00:20:21,450 --> 00:20:23,460
never really showed much interest
in women before.

213
00:20:24,660 --> 00:20:27,130
I even started to wonder
if he had a crush on me.

214
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:39,640
It's all set.

215
00:20:41,410 --> 00:20:42,410
What do you mean?

216
00:20:44,740 --> 00:20:45,910
You seem happy.

217
00:20:49,450 --> 00:20:50,880
Do you have any jinxes, by any chance?

218
00:20:51,950 --> 00:20:53,080
What kind of jinx?

219
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:54,950
The kind that makes you want to dance.

220
00:20:55,650 --> 00:20:57,360
If only music were playing now...

221
00:20:57,720 --> 00:20:59,820
I have the sudden urge to waltz right now.

222
00:21:03,430 --> 00:21:04,430
With me?

223
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:07,370
Yes.

224
00:21:58,550 --> 00:22:01,550
Spring is right around the corner,
and yet a blizzard hit us.

225
00:22:02,390 --> 00:22:03,790
You know how to waltz?

226
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:05,990
I am an actress, after all.

227
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:08,360
I can sort of pull off the tango too.

228
00:22:09,260 --> 00:22:12,260
I wish I'd learned it
for a day like today.

229
00:22:14,730 --> 00:22:17,270
I heard your mother was
a double bass player.

230
00:22:17,740 --> 00:22:18,740
She was.

231
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:20,940
Ju Shin...

232
00:22:21,540 --> 00:22:23,680
didn't just say good things about me,
did he?

233
00:22:25,040 --> 00:22:26,850
He said you were
his most troublesome friend.

234
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:35,420
Is my makeup too much?

235
00:22:37,190 --> 00:22:38,190
No.

236
00:22:48,630 --> 00:22:49,770
Why are you standing out here?

237
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:54,410
It's hot in this dress.

238
00:22:56,470 --> 00:22:59,240
(Our deepest condolences
to the bereaved family)

239
00:23:29,310 --> 00:23:30,310
(Family waiting room)

240
00:23:39,020 --> 00:23:41,050
Push my meeting with Mr. Jo to tomorrow.

241
00:23:41,790 --> 00:23:44,160
- The cross shoot is at 3 p.m.
- Send Manager Choi.

242
00:23:45,190 --> 00:23:47,890
- Let's go pay our respects, Jin Ju.
- I've already been.

243
00:23:48,230 --> 00:23:50,330
- When?
- Last night.

244
00:23:56,940 --> 00:23:57,940
Momo.

245
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:00,370
Did I do the right thing?

246
00:24:01,540 --> 00:24:02,940
Do I really have to let you go like this?

247
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:17,220
Do you think you'll be able to sleep?

248
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:20,590
Just talk to me like you talk to Momo.

249
00:25:20,990 --> 00:25:22,190
If anyone heard you...

250
00:25:22,550 --> 00:25:24,160
It's not like we'll be seeing each other
much longer anyway.

251
00:25:29,790 --> 00:25:32,130
You can say you broke up naturally
by next year anyway.

252
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:36,100
Go.

253
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:40,410
I'm going to keep drinking
until I fall asleep.

254
00:25:42,470 --> 00:25:44,340
I'm really starting to feel
like I'm becoming Momo.

255
00:25:45,040 --> 00:25:48,650
She's not some stranger.
She's my own flesh and blood.

256
00:25:49,450 --> 00:25:52,780
I am Momo, and Momo is me.

257
00:25:56,350 --> 00:25:57,860
Puppies and wine...

258
00:25:58,420 --> 00:26:00,430
are the deity's gift to humanity.

259
00:26:07,030 --> 00:26:08,030
You're not having any?

260
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:09,470
I drove.

261
00:26:09,730 --> 00:26:11,040
We can call for a ride.

262
00:26:15,270 --> 00:26:16,570
When I look in the mirror,

263
00:26:16,980 --> 00:26:18,910
it doesn't feel like Momo's dead.

264
00:26:20,010 --> 00:26:24,150
It just feels like
I'm looking right at my daughter.

265
00:26:27,590 --> 00:26:28,950
Hyun Ran Hee is the one who died.

266
00:26:31,420 --> 00:26:33,090
They say there's more than meets the eye,

267
00:26:33,630 --> 00:26:35,660
you should just accept what you see.

268
00:26:36,330 --> 00:26:38,000
There's no need to overthink it.

269
00:26:45,540 --> 00:26:46,840
It's too quiet.

270
00:26:52,010 --> 00:26:54,280
He has such a noble brow.

271
00:26:54,980 --> 00:26:56,850
So aristocratic.

272
00:26:57,350 --> 00:26:59,080
Like fine white porcelain.

273
00:27:01,820 --> 00:27:02,820
Leaving?

274
00:27:07,030 --> 00:27:08,530
Loosen your tie before you go.

275
00:27:08,860 --> 00:27:10,460
It looks so tight and suffocating.

276
00:27:39,620 --> 00:27:40,990
Go abroad for a while.

277
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:42,760
It's me.

278
00:27:46,030 --> 00:27:47,230
Why on earth?

279
00:27:48,330 --> 00:27:50,000
(CEO James Ha)

280
00:27:51,940 --> 00:27:54,670
- Hello?
- Hi, it's James.

281
00:27:54,870 --> 00:27:56,170
Mr. Ha. Hello.

282
00:27:56,370 --> 00:28:00,210
With Momo's mother away,
I'm sure you don't have an appetite.

283
00:28:00,410 --> 00:28:02,580
I figured you'd be starving at home alone,

284
00:28:02,650 --> 00:28:04,120
so I made some side dishes.

285
00:28:04,920 --> 00:28:08,120
Sending them by a manager felt impersonal,
and I was worried about you.

286
00:28:08,950 --> 00:28:09,950
I see.

287
00:28:10,660 --> 00:28:12,820
Would it be alright if I dropped by?

288
00:28:13,220 --> 00:28:15,760
They aren't dishes we have to eat today,
are they?

289
00:28:15,830 --> 00:28:17,060
Of course not.

290
00:28:17,330 --> 00:28:18,660
Are you on your way home?

291
00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:20,400
Are you off work yet?

292
00:28:20,700 --> 00:28:21,800
I'm about to.

293
00:28:23,230 --> 00:28:24,240
Have a seat.

294
00:28:26,870 --> 00:28:28,740
Do you have any food at home?

295
00:28:29,540 --> 00:28:31,980
I'm not that interested in food.

296
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:36,450
Why not? Eating is extremely important.

297
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:39,780
That's no good.

298
00:28:39,780 --> 00:28:42,250
Eat well in your youth to age well.

299
00:28:42,350 --> 00:28:46,060
- Hippocrates said it best.
- "You are what you eat"?

300
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:47,130
Exactly.

301
00:28:50,960 --> 00:28:52,500
Do you have a dog?

302
00:28:53,360 --> 00:28:55,200
I lost her, the year before last.

303
00:29:01,740 --> 00:29:03,310
Do you like dogs?

304
00:29:03,910 --> 00:29:05,110
Of course.

305
00:29:05,940 --> 00:29:07,550
Her name was Oiji?

306
00:29:08,250 --> 00:29:09,780
They give out awards for this?

307
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:11,550
Yes.

308
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:14,020
She had been through a lot.

309
00:29:26,260 --> 00:29:27,730
I think I taste some lemon.

310
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:29,800
That, and some other healthy stuff.

311
00:29:30,130 --> 00:29:31,570
Stay for a quick dinner.

312
00:29:31,800 --> 00:29:34,810
- No, I'm fine.
- It's no trouble. It's already made.

313
00:30:02,630 --> 00:30:05,900
It's not from a package.
I slow-cooked it with premium beef.

314
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,510
You're so busy, but you made it yourself?

315
00:30:07,570 --> 00:30:09,370
They say, "If you want it done right,
do it yourself."

316
00:30:10,270 --> 00:30:11,510
I've heard that one.

317
00:30:12,010 --> 00:30:13,180
Add salt if you need it.

318
00:30:17,980 --> 00:30:19,150
Thank you for the meal.

319
00:30:25,020 --> 00:30:26,720
- It's not bland at all.
- Good.

320
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:28,760
It's perfect. I actually prefer less salt.

321
00:30:28,830 --> 00:30:30,760
That's the way to do it.

322
00:30:37,340 --> 00:30:39,670
Wouldn't it be nice to live this way?

323
00:30:39,670 --> 00:30:41,340
I'd treat her like a queen,

324
00:30:41,410 --> 00:30:43,240
and she wouldn't have to lift a finger.

325
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:50,850
Gosh, look how she enjoys her food.

326
00:30:52,950 --> 00:30:55,820
She didn't seem depressed at all.

327
00:30:56,450 --> 00:31:00,360
Right. Maybe if her career
as Momo was failing...

328
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:04,030
- She was about to get married...
- I know.

329
00:31:04,030 --> 00:31:05,200
She had a top-star daughter,

330
00:31:05,260 --> 00:31:07,900
who was engaged to a catch
like Director Shin,

331
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:09,300
and her gallery was doing well.

332
00:31:09,570 --> 00:31:11,770
Do you think having no worries
is a problem in itself?

333
00:31:13,200 --> 00:31:14,640
How is Momo getting by?

334
00:31:17,310 --> 00:31:18,310
By the way,

335
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:21,810
since you're Yong Joong's older brother,
you don't have to be so formal with me.

336
00:31:22,850 --> 00:31:24,880
- You sure?
- Yes.

337
00:31:24,950 --> 00:31:27,450
That makes sense,
since you're so close with Yong Joong.

338
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:31,060
Maybe she'll feel that way with me.

339
00:31:32,720 --> 00:31:35,660
- Ha Yong Joong's car is now arriving.
- He's here for the side dishes.

340
00:31:36,890 --> 00:31:39,360
It's all the same stuff, so take one each.

341
00:31:39,660 --> 00:31:43,570
- One for me too?
- They're better if you make a big batch.

342
00:31:43,700 --> 00:31:46,100
I'll drop Ba Ra off and take this to Momo.

343
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:47,610
And why would you do that?

344
00:31:48,070 --> 00:31:50,440
- Does Ba Ra even have her car here?
- She can take a cab.

345
00:31:50,740 --> 00:31:51,740
Right?

346
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:54,750
You're going to make a reporter
run errands for an actress?

347
00:31:54,810 --> 00:31:57,110
Their jobs have nothing to do with it.
They were close friends.

348
00:31:57,620 --> 00:31:58,680
Weren't you?

349
00:32:00,220 --> 00:32:03,960
- Anyway.
- She's alone at home with no helper.

350
00:32:04,190 --> 00:32:06,190
I can just ask her
to come down to the lobby.

351
00:32:06,420 --> 00:32:10,160
Is Momo just some random person?
What if Ju Shin gets the wrong idea?

352
00:32:10,230 --> 00:32:12,460
It could get awkward for Momo too.

353
00:32:12,800 --> 00:32:14,330
It's just an errand for you.
What's the big deal?

354
00:32:15,030 --> 00:32:18,070
I didn't ask you to. Leave me out of it.
Fine then.

355
00:32:18,870 --> 00:32:20,540
I'll just eat it myself then. Forget it.

356
00:32:21,810 --> 00:32:24,310
I think he's just worried about her.

357
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:26,440
That's my point.

358
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:28,650
Why is he so worried
about his best friend's fiancee?

359
00:32:28,710 --> 00:32:30,650
Ju Shin will take care of her.

360
00:32:30,650 --> 00:32:32,220
You think Ju Shin cooks and cleans?

361
00:32:32,520 --> 00:32:33,650
You think he has time?

362
00:32:33,650 --> 00:32:35,290
- If he had three bodies...
- And you?

363
00:32:35,620 --> 00:32:36,650
Do you have time?

364
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:38,390
Imagine how hard it must be
for her right now.

365
00:32:39,320 --> 00:32:40,730
We went through it too.

366
00:32:41,530 --> 00:32:42,530
Have you forgotten?

367
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:49,300
Let's go see her tomorrow morning.

368
00:32:49,530 --> 00:32:51,340
I can't just ignore this either.

369
00:32:51,670 --> 00:32:53,500
It's too late tonight.

370
00:33:06,550 --> 00:33:07,550
Her address.

371
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:16,160
You don't get it either, do you?

372
00:33:31,910 --> 00:33:34,080
Sorry, all I have is water and coffee.

373
00:33:36,050 --> 00:33:37,150
I'm thirsty.

374
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:52,400
That guy...

375
00:33:53,060 --> 00:33:54,670
He's been doing better than I expected.

376
00:33:57,170 --> 00:33:58,940
Being a bodyguard pays pretty well.

377
00:34:00,370 --> 00:34:01,570
It's hazard pay.

378
00:34:04,180 --> 00:34:06,180
Once I get the new place,
I'll sell this place...

379
00:34:06,180 --> 00:34:08,180
and donate the money in An Hee's name.

380
00:34:09,950 --> 00:34:11,650
You know I can help you out.

381
00:34:14,790 --> 00:34:16,490
Am I treating you differently from An Hee?

382
00:34:18,160 --> 00:34:20,990
I've faced so much discrimination,
I don't want to even hear that word.

383
00:34:24,660 --> 00:34:26,330
Lawyer Tae Won Young said he knew you.

384
00:34:29,070 --> 00:34:30,630
I signed a contract with his law firm,

385
00:34:31,170 --> 00:34:32,670
and while we were talking
about that interview article...

386
00:34:35,770 --> 00:34:37,710
I heard he got remarried.

387
00:34:39,710 --> 00:34:40,910
Is he happy?

388
00:34:41,410 --> 00:34:42,480
He's remarried?

389
00:34:43,480 --> 00:34:46,150
- What did he say about me?
- Nothing really.

390
00:34:46,150 --> 00:34:48,090
An associate was there.

391
00:34:48,490 --> 00:34:49,790
Do you two have some kind of history?

392
00:35:06,100 --> 00:35:07,540
Are you Ye Jeong's father?

393
00:35:07,570 --> 00:35:08,610
Yes.

394
00:35:10,340 --> 00:35:11,580
I'm here because of Ye Jeong.

395
00:35:12,710 --> 00:35:14,910
I was on my way to the police station,
but I came here instead.

396
00:35:18,380 --> 00:35:19,420
Ye Jeong!

397
00:35:20,450 --> 00:35:22,820
Your father said
he was going to bed early.

398
00:35:22,890 --> 00:35:24,120
Tell her to come downstairs.

399
00:35:35,500 --> 00:35:36,500
Sit.

400
00:35:39,200 --> 00:35:40,600
Let's talk about this inside.

401
00:35:46,110 --> 00:35:47,680
- I'm home, Father.
- Alright.

402
00:35:49,680 --> 00:35:50,680
Who are you?

403
00:35:52,980 --> 00:35:54,290
My name is Geum Ba Ra.

404
00:35:54,820 --> 00:35:56,650
I'm not in the same class
as Tae Ye Jeong, though.

405
00:36:05,060 --> 00:36:06,330
Sit down, all of you.

406
00:36:08,170 --> 00:36:09,670
Bring something out.

407
00:36:10,270 --> 00:36:11,270
I'm fine.

408
00:36:16,540 --> 00:36:18,780
I grew up at an orphanage...

409
00:36:18,780 --> 00:36:20,580
with a girl from my class, Kim Jin Ju.

410
00:36:21,310 --> 00:36:23,450
Do you know Nua Children's Home?

411
00:36:23,850 --> 00:36:25,750
The one behind the cathedral?

412
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:30,090
Yes. Jin Ju and I have been roommates
our whole lives,

413
00:36:30,620 --> 00:36:32,990
but Tae Ye Jeong constantly bullies her.

414
00:36:32,990 --> 00:36:35,560
Today, she even hit her with two others.

415
00:36:38,230 --> 00:36:40,360
- It's over and done with.
- How can it be over?

416
00:36:40,430 --> 00:36:41,530
I ended it.

417
00:36:41,630 --> 00:36:43,430
But you're the one
who started this up again.

418
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:46,300
- I got hit too!
- Quiet!

419
00:36:48,140 --> 00:36:49,870
I saw the three of them
ganging up on Jin Ju,

420
00:36:49,940 --> 00:36:52,940
so I had no choice but to hit them
a few times to defend her.

421
00:36:53,610 --> 00:36:55,750
They started coming after me too.
What was I supposed to do?

422
00:36:56,350 --> 00:36:58,350
Growing up in an orphanage
is already hard enough,

423
00:36:58,780 --> 00:37:00,350
and it's a painful wound.

424
00:37:02,190 --> 00:37:05,620
But they ridiculed us,
calling us brats with no parents.

425
00:37:06,590 --> 00:37:08,430
But I endured it and put an end to it.

426
00:37:10,190 --> 00:37:13,260
Did you know your daughter bullies kids
who are easy targets?

427
00:37:15,500 --> 00:37:16,530
I didn't even...

428
00:37:17,470 --> 00:37:18,770
That's not what a student does.

429
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:21,340
She does monstrous things
without a second thought.

430
00:37:21,610 --> 00:37:24,780
Have you ever thought about what it's like
to be on the receiving end?

431
00:37:24,780 --> 00:37:25,780
You're lying.

432
00:37:27,110 --> 00:37:28,980
- Don't exaggerate.
- You think I'm exaggerating?

433
00:37:29,380 --> 00:37:30,380
So...

434
00:37:30,710 --> 00:37:33,880
Are you saying my Ye Jeong
did this to you?

435
00:37:35,390 --> 00:37:36,450
Her "husband" did.

436
00:37:36,890 --> 00:37:37,890
Hey!

437
00:37:39,860 --> 00:37:41,790
It's just a stupid joke
among the kids at school.

438
00:37:41,860 --> 00:37:43,560
I heard it clearly. Yoon Seong Tae.

439
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:44,860
He's a senior at our school,

440
00:37:45,030 --> 00:37:46,800
and he said,
"You scratched my wife's face."

441
00:37:46,800 --> 00:37:47,830
What...

442
00:37:47,830 --> 00:37:48,900
Father.

443
00:37:51,900 --> 00:37:54,070
He's just an older guy
who tends to overreact.

444
00:37:54,940 --> 00:37:56,370
Is doing this to me "overreacting?"

445
00:37:56,740 --> 00:37:59,580
So those guys you know just kidnapped me
as a group because they were bored?

446
00:37:59,740 --> 00:38:00,840
And then did this to me?

447
00:38:02,480 --> 00:38:05,050
- You provoked them!
- I don't know what you told them,

448
00:38:05,820 --> 00:38:06,950
but they completely lost it.

449
00:38:07,420 --> 00:38:09,020
Did you or did you not hear...

450
00:38:09,020 --> 00:38:10,220
four senior boys screaming
that I scratched your face...

451
00:38:10,220 --> 00:38:12,520
as they began to strip me and beat me?

452
00:38:13,290 --> 00:38:15,590
You were smiling, encouraging them
to "teach me a real lesson."

453
00:38:16,490 --> 00:38:18,200
Tae Ye Jeong hit me over the head
with a piece of lumber.

454
00:38:18,460 --> 00:38:20,230
Come feel my head and see how bad it is.

455
00:38:21,030 --> 00:38:22,530
You... You little...

456
00:38:22,800 --> 00:38:25,370
Did you not know your daughter was running
around doing things like this?

457
00:38:28,770 --> 00:38:29,770
Say something!

458
00:38:30,770 --> 00:38:31,780
I'm sorry.

459
00:38:33,110 --> 00:38:34,950
- Go to your room.
- No.

460
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:37,410
I'm not done talking yet.

461
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:40,220
I...

462
00:38:40,950 --> 00:38:42,290
know how to fight.

463
00:38:42,750 --> 00:38:45,120
For self-defense,
so I wouldn't just get beaten up.

464
00:38:46,220 --> 00:38:48,330
If I hadn't held back with every ounce
of my strength today,

465
00:38:49,130 --> 00:38:50,890
Tae Ye Jeong would be
in a full-body cast right now.

466
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:53,800
Big deal.

467
00:38:54,530 --> 00:38:55,970
You always go around dropping
your dad's name, don't you?

468
00:38:56,700 --> 00:38:58,170
Saying he's a lawyer
at a big firm in Seoul.

469
00:38:58,670 --> 00:39:00,040
So who's going to sue you
after you beat them up?

470
00:39:00,870 --> 00:39:03,370
I know.
Teachers walk on eggshells around you.

471
00:39:04,410 --> 00:39:06,740
And you've got top thug Yoon Seong Tae
as your "husband."

472
00:39:06,740 --> 00:39:08,510
He's not my husband, you witch!

473
00:39:09,110 --> 00:39:10,110
Shut it.

474
00:39:10,380 --> 00:39:13,680
To think she was born
just to bring shame to this family.

475
00:39:15,020 --> 00:39:16,350
There are many other victims.

476
00:39:16,890 --> 00:39:19,160
And they will all carry
those deep scars for life.

477
00:39:20,320 --> 00:39:21,660
Okay, we understand.

478
00:39:22,260 --> 00:39:24,760
We'll punish her severely
so she never does it again.

479
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:28,630
But it's the middle of the night,
and with his blood pressure...

480
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:30,430
The reason I came all this way is this.

481
00:39:33,300 --> 00:39:35,140
I want you to hit her ten times,
right in front of me.

482
00:39:36,870 --> 00:39:41,180
Or, I'll hit her myself, just as much
as Seong Tae's crew hit me today,

483
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:43,150
and I'll turn myself in to the police.

484
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:48,090
To be honest,

485
00:39:49,150 --> 00:39:50,790
I don't really have much to live for.

486
00:39:53,390 --> 00:39:55,790
Just like Ye Jeong taunted me
and hit me where it hurt,

487
00:39:56,860 --> 00:39:58,330
my own parents abandoned me.

488
00:39:59,400 --> 00:40:01,500
So why would I have any will to live
or attachment to my life?

489
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:06,700
I grew up never once getting
to say "Mom" or "Dad" like everyone else.

490
00:40:07,540 --> 00:40:10,310
Can any of you even imagine
how that feels?

491
00:40:12,610 --> 00:40:14,710
I only hit you back a few times
in self-defense.

492
00:40:15,250 --> 00:40:18,780
You got so mad over a couple of hits
you sent your thug "husband" after me.

493
00:40:19,980 --> 00:40:24,150
I don't know if he's really your man
or if it's just for show.

494
00:40:25,220 --> 00:40:27,120
You shouldn't just say things like that...

495
00:40:27,190 --> 00:40:29,560
You've done a fine job
raising your only daughter.

496
00:40:31,930 --> 00:40:33,460
Try to imagine how the kids...

497
00:40:34,230 --> 00:40:35,630
you tormented and beat up must feel.

498
00:40:36,730 --> 00:40:40,140
They've likely imagined tearing you apart
a thousand times over in their minds.

499
00:40:42,070 --> 00:40:43,240
Because that's what I was doing today.

500
00:40:45,580 --> 00:40:46,880
I barely held myself back...

501
00:40:48,310 --> 00:40:49,710
and came here to deal
with this rationally.

502
00:40:51,350 --> 00:40:52,420
I'm sorry.

503
00:40:52,550 --> 00:40:53,750
We understand, so please go.

504
00:40:54,650 --> 00:40:56,950
- Something like today will never...
- You can't even hit her ten times?

505
00:40:58,060 --> 00:41:00,990
We'll discuss it
and discipline her ourselves.

506
00:41:01,120 --> 00:41:02,160
In front of me.

507
00:41:04,760 --> 00:41:05,760
Only then,

508
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:08,170
I think I'll be able to live with this.

509
00:41:09,730 --> 00:41:11,240
Go get me something.

510
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:14,000
Hurry up.

511
00:41:14,910 --> 00:41:17,710
There's nothing suitable here.
I'll have something prepared by tomorrow.

512
00:41:17,770 --> 00:41:20,010
- We have the golf club.
- Father!

513
00:41:20,280 --> 00:41:21,280
I was wrong!

514
00:41:21,350 --> 00:41:24,780
If saying you were wrong could erase
the scars and injuries I have,

515
00:41:25,820 --> 00:41:26,820
I'd accept your apology.

516
00:41:31,790 --> 00:41:34,630
You hit her ten times.

517
00:41:34,990 --> 00:41:38,600
- Father!
- You hit her ten times,

518
00:41:39,930 --> 00:41:41,770
and her father will get a beating from me.

519
00:41:43,100 --> 00:41:45,300
You need to see this with your own eyes.

520
00:41:45,440 --> 00:41:46,740
All because of this one girl!

521
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:49,040
Grandfather, I'll turn over a new leaf.
Starting today.

522
00:41:49,110 --> 00:41:50,810
What exactly is your relationship
with that punk?

523
00:41:51,070 --> 00:41:52,280
You're not even dry behind the ears.

524
00:41:52,610 --> 00:41:54,510
Please, I swear.

525
00:41:54,580 --> 00:41:57,110
He just always acts like he's flirting.

526
00:41:57,350 --> 00:41:58,720
There's nothing going on between us.

527
00:41:58,720 --> 00:42:00,420
He's just a bodyguard.

528
00:42:00,520 --> 00:42:02,420
If my orphanage friend
hadn't been there today,

529
00:42:02,420 --> 00:42:03,850
who knows what would've happened?

530
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:06,260
- They were trying to strip me...
- Hey! Get over here. Now.

531
00:42:06,320 --> 00:42:07,320
Dad, I'm sorry! I was wrong!

532
00:42:07,590 --> 00:42:10,690
- Honey.
- What a fine mess this family is in.

533
00:42:10,990 --> 00:42:13,000
You feed her well,
dress her in nice clothes,

534
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:16,100
and you think just throwing money
at her studies is how you raise a child?

535
00:42:16,500 --> 00:42:17,500
Darn it.

536
00:42:17,770 --> 00:42:18,900
- Grandfather!
- Honey.

537
00:42:20,500 --> 00:42:22,570
- Grandfather.
- Father.

538
00:42:24,470 --> 00:42:26,510
No, honey, you have to stop him.

539
00:42:48,030 --> 00:42:49,330
Maybe it was karma,

540
00:42:50,970 --> 00:42:52,940
but two months later, Tae Ye Jeong died.

541
00:42:54,340 --> 00:42:56,040
At their vacation home on Jeju Island,

542
00:42:57,210 --> 00:42:58,380
on the beach right in front of the house.

543
00:43:02,910 --> 00:43:05,920
Because I didn't have parents
and grew up in an orphanage,

544
00:43:07,250 --> 00:43:10,450
I went through so much
and was always looked down on.

545
00:43:12,420 --> 00:43:14,960
Sometimes I wonder
if the expressions I show people...

546
00:43:15,690 --> 00:43:16,730
and the emotions I display...

547
00:43:17,790 --> 00:43:20,500
are all just an act.

548
00:43:23,500 --> 00:43:25,100
When I felt so worthless,

549
00:43:25,740 --> 00:43:27,670
there were people
who genuinely cared for me.

550
00:43:29,370 --> 00:43:30,370
There was An Hee,

551
00:43:31,940 --> 00:43:32,940
and there was you.

552
00:43:36,550 --> 00:43:39,050
An Hee took care of me
because we were in the same boat,

553
00:43:40,020 --> 00:43:41,020
but you...

554
00:43:42,250 --> 00:43:44,250
genuinely adored me when I was just a kid.

555
00:43:47,320 --> 00:43:49,560
It was the first time
I had ever really felt it.

556
00:43:50,060 --> 00:43:53,100
"Oh, so this is what it's like
to be adored."

557
00:43:54,930 --> 00:43:56,130
It was only for a few months, but...

558
00:44:00,840 --> 00:44:03,940
I've always missed that warmth.

559
00:44:04,910 --> 00:44:06,840
Thinking of it helped me
get through the hard times.

560
00:44:14,690 --> 00:44:15,690
So even if you...

561
00:44:16,720 --> 00:44:19,190
like and love a wicked witch,

562
00:44:21,460 --> 00:44:23,790
I feel like it's my place
to try to understand.

563
00:44:25,600 --> 00:44:27,100
Maybe no one else has to,

564
00:44:29,270 --> 00:44:30,270
but I do.

565
00:44:39,440 --> 00:44:40,440
I'll always...

566
00:44:42,050 --> 00:44:43,050
be by your side.

567
00:44:44,680 --> 00:44:46,280
We'll never be apart again.

568
00:44:48,190 --> 00:44:49,190
Forever?

569
00:44:51,050 --> 00:44:52,060
Forever.

570
00:44:53,460 --> 00:44:55,190
You don't have to force it.

571
00:44:56,360 --> 00:44:57,390
I'm not.

572
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:02,630
My brother and I aren't related by blood,
but he's the only brother I have.

573
00:45:05,500 --> 00:45:06,500
It's the same with you.

574
00:45:09,110 --> 00:45:10,270
Just promise me one thing.

575
00:45:12,340 --> 00:45:13,380
What?

576
00:45:13,380 --> 00:45:14,780
When things get tough and you struggle,

577
00:45:16,280 --> 00:45:17,810
don't try to bear it all on your own.

578
00:45:19,050 --> 00:45:20,350
You've got me now.

579
00:45:21,650 --> 00:45:23,250
I'll be content with just having you...

580
00:45:24,450 --> 00:45:26,390
by my side or watching from afar.

581
00:45:28,190 --> 00:45:29,260
My dear Ba Ra...

582
00:45:30,560 --> 00:45:32,200
You've done so well for yourself.

583
00:45:34,330 --> 00:45:35,930
The more I think about it,
the prouder I am of you,

584
00:45:38,540 --> 00:45:39,540
and I'm so grateful.

585
00:45:45,680 --> 00:45:47,580
Why'd An Hee have to die,
leaving us behind?

586
00:45:48,550 --> 00:45:50,150
Imagine how great it would be
if he were with us now.

587
00:45:54,120 --> 00:45:55,490
I have a favor to ask, too.

588
00:45:57,150 --> 00:45:58,160
What is it?

589
00:45:58,760 --> 00:46:00,020
Live a long, long life.

590
00:46:01,890 --> 00:46:02,890
Promise me.

591
00:46:06,800 --> 00:46:07,800
All right.

592
00:46:08,770 --> 00:46:10,830
I have to grant any wish
my big girl asks of me.

593
00:46:12,940 --> 00:46:14,640
Just don't ask for the moon.

594
00:46:15,710 --> 00:46:17,470
Some things are just impossible.

595
00:46:32,190 --> 00:46:33,560
If you find her,

596
00:46:33,890 --> 00:46:35,930
tell her...

597
00:46:36,630 --> 00:46:37,630
that her mom was so, so sorry.

598
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:46,340
You have to find her. No matter what.

599
00:46:58,050 --> 00:46:59,980
You've been on a real roll lately.

600
00:47:00,350 --> 00:47:02,220
It's been one Geum Ba Ra exclusive
after another.

601
00:47:08,120 --> 00:47:10,830
(A sentence can change the world.
Relentless pursuit of truth)

602
00:47:13,300 --> 00:47:14,300
Get in.

603
00:47:17,400 --> 00:47:19,100
(A sentence can change the world.
Relentless pursuit of truth)

604
00:47:19,600 --> 00:47:21,540
The other outlets are busy
just copying each other's stories,

605
00:47:24,210 --> 00:47:28,250
and since you're so short-staffed,
it must be hard just to keep up.

606
00:47:28,310 --> 00:47:29,310
You're doing a great job.

607
00:47:29,580 --> 00:47:30,580
Not at all, sir.

608
00:47:31,150 --> 00:47:32,550
I'm keeping an eye on you.

609
00:47:33,420 --> 00:47:34,420
Thank you, sir.

610
00:47:35,850 --> 00:47:38,760
Sorry, Yong Joong.
I just got an urgent assignment.

611
00:47:39,490 --> 00:47:40,920
Don't apologize to me.

612
00:47:43,060 --> 00:47:44,060
Okay?

613
00:47:45,160 --> 00:47:46,160
Alright.

614
00:47:46,660 --> 00:47:48,200
And you've picked up another cute habit.

615
00:47:50,900 --> 00:47:53,700
At some point,
you dropped the formalities with me.

616
00:47:54,570 --> 00:47:56,910
My gosh, what's gotten into me?

617
00:47:57,210 --> 00:47:58,210
That's why I like it.

618
00:47:59,180 --> 00:48:00,310
You think I'm a pushover, don't you?

619
00:48:00,910 --> 00:48:01,910
No, that's not it.

620
00:48:02,210 --> 00:48:03,210
Try that again.

621
00:48:04,850 --> 00:48:05,850
No.

622
00:48:05,850 --> 00:48:07,650
I'm the guy
you're most comfortable being with.

623
00:48:11,990 --> 00:48:12,990
Get back to it.

624
00:48:14,060 --> 00:48:15,230
Yes.

625
00:48:15,230 --> 00:48:16,390
"Yes?"

626
00:48:16,690 --> 00:48:17,960
Okay, Yong Joong.

627
00:48:19,500 --> 00:48:20,500
You hang up first.

628
00:48:21,300 --> 00:48:22,500
Here's your coffee.

629
00:49:00,170 --> 00:49:01,170
Welcome.

630
00:49:05,380 --> 00:49:06,380
Here...

631
00:49:07,910 --> 00:49:11,050
Should I put this in the fridge for now?
Is there room?

632
00:49:12,450 --> 00:49:14,620
I'll sort it out and put it away...

633
00:49:16,290 --> 00:49:17,350
Have you been eating properly?

634
00:49:19,020 --> 00:49:20,890
Don't you have anyone you can call?

635
00:49:21,690 --> 00:49:22,830
My manager stops by every now and then...

636
00:49:27,060 --> 00:49:28,060
What about Ju Shin?

637
00:49:29,730 --> 00:49:31,840
How about staying somewhere else
for a little while?

638
00:49:36,810 --> 00:49:37,870
We're...

639
00:49:38,880 --> 00:49:40,310
all in the same boat.

640
00:49:41,510 --> 00:49:43,650
Ju Shin, you,

641
00:49:44,480 --> 00:49:45,550
and me.

642
00:49:47,720 --> 00:49:48,850
Someone once said...

643
00:49:49,890 --> 00:49:51,650
that if you don't have parents,
you're an orphan.

644
00:49:53,020 --> 00:49:55,930
When did your parents pass away?

645
00:49:57,090 --> 00:49:58,800
My dad passed away
when I was in second grade.

646
00:50:00,160 --> 00:50:01,360
And my mom passed away
during my senior year of high school.

647
00:50:02,100 --> 00:50:04,270
So I know how you feel
better than anyone, Momo.

648
00:50:06,270 --> 00:50:07,740
I know how hard it must be
for you right now.

649
00:50:17,510 --> 00:50:20,550
When my mother passed away,
I couldn't even really cry.

650
00:50:22,420 --> 00:50:23,750
My brother cried a lot, though.

651
00:50:25,260 --> 00:50:26,820
Isn't this the part
where he gives me a hug?

652
00:50:37,170 --> 00:50:39,040
Did Ju Shin tell you about my brother?

653
00:50:41,170 --> 00:50:44,640
James told me himself once.

654
00:50:45,510 --> 00:50:47,980
That he was adopted in elementary school.

655
00:50:52,120 --> 00:50:55,450
I heard James's birth mother
and your mother...

656
00:50:56,290 --> 00:50:58,790
were in the same orchestra, right?

657
00:50:59,120 --> 00:51:00,120
Yes.

658
00:51:03,760 --> 00:51:05,360
It might sound like a cliche,
but it's true.

659
00:51:06,430 --> 00:51:07,730
As time goes on,

660
00:51:09,000 --> 00:51:10,430
the sadness does fade.

661
00:51:12,440 --> 00:51:14,140
For now, all you can do is endure it.

662
00:51:14,670 --> 00:51:15,870
There's no other way.

663
00:51:19,810 --> 00:51:20,880
Thank you.

664
00:51:31,550 --> 00:51:34,760
I bought the Laketop penthouse.
Would you like to stay there for a while?

665
00:51:35,590 --> 00:51:36,830
What's the point of leaving it empty?

666
00:51:36,830 --> 00:51:39,100
I was worried tenants would ruin it,
so it's empty.

667
00:51:40,400 --> 00:51:43,600
The 18-million-dollar Laketop penthouse?

668
00:51:49,140 --> 00:51:50,170
Goodbye.

669
00:51:50,410 --> 00:51:51,880
Think about it and text me.

670
00:51:53,680 --> 00:51:54,680
Okay.

671
00:52:14,030 --> 00:52:15,170
Yes!

672
00:52:20,600 --> 00:52:23,610
That was the most delicious breakfast
I've had in a long time.

673
00:52:23,870 --> 00:52:24,940
Thank you.

674
00:52:29,280 --> 00:52:32,350
- What's got you in such a good mood?
- It's Ms. Geum Ba Ra.

675
00:52:32,680 --> 00:52:34,020
She said she loved my cooking.

676
00:52:34,080 --> 00:52:37,220
You would've made a killing
in the restaurant business.

677
00:52:37,490 --> 00:52:39,620
You dote on your brother,

678
00:52:39,620 --> 00:52:40,990
so no wonder
he doesn't think about getting married.

679
00:52:41,290 --> 00:52:42,490
He has everything he needs.

680
00:52:43,830 --> 00:52:45,730
How many of our pieces got into
Sera Lauren magazine?

681
00:52:48,570 --> 00:52:50,500
(Ha Yong Joong, CEO of WorldNet)

682
00:52:53,940 --> 00:52:57,510
(Ha Yong Joong, Developer of
Record-Breaking Mega-Hit "Lost Knights")

683
00:53:03,350 --> 00:53:04,380
(Ba Ra)

684
00:53:04,480 --> 00:53:06,120
I know this must be really hard,

685
00:53:06,880 --> 00:53:08,620
but people are curious.

686
00:53:09,190 --> 00:53:11,920
So it'd be good to briefly announce
your future plans.

687
00:53:12,720 --> 00:53:14,620
That should quiet down the media, too.

688
00:53:15,560 --> 00:53:17,360
I can drop by for a bit,

689
00:53:17,760 --> 00:53:19,730
or we could meet somewhere
you're comfortable.

690
00:53:23,100 --> 00:53:24,270
Are you getting any sleep?

691
00:53:25,770 --> 00:53:28,540
Only a little after I've completely
exhausted myself.

692
00:53:30,210 --> 00:53:31,510
Are you cleaning up her things alone?

693
00:53:34,380 --> 00:53:35,710
I'd like to help.

694
00:53:36,450 --> 00:53:37,450
I'm okay.

695
00:53:39,580 --> 00:53:41,350
Last year, on the day we were
supposed to meet,

696
00:53:41,750 --> 00:53:44,520
I saw your mother at the airport,
and she was so cheerful.

697
00:53:45,860 --> 00:53:48,290
Did you have any idea she was struggling?

698
00:53:52,100 --> 00:53:54,800
Then why did you cut off all contact
for so long...

699
00:53:56,200 --> 00:53:59,470
The moment I let my guard down,
I got burnt out.

700
00:54:01,140 --> 00:54:02,970
I spent a few months in Lausanne, too.

701
00:54:04,510 --> 00:54:05,640
Lausanne, in Switzerland?

702
00:54:09,010 --> 00:54:10,450
I need you to run a story
on my retirement.

703
00:54:12,080 --> 00:54:14,320
Wouldn't it be better to keep busy?

704
00:54:15,250 --> 00:54:16,390
I don't have it in me.

705
00:54:16,920 --> 00:54:17,920
Who would I even be doing it for...?

706
00:54:18,790 --> 00:54:20,420
Your fans are going to be so disappointed.

707
00:54:23,090 --> 00:54:25,060
Is your wedding with Director Shin
still on?

708
00:54:26,660 --> 00:54:28,100
You don't have to talk about it
if you don't want to.

709
00:54:28,900 --> 00:54:30,470
It's just so absurd.

710
00:54:31,170 --> 00:54:32,740
Professor Shin, who was so healthy...

711
00:54:36,310 --> 00:54:39,710
I mean, Ju Shin's father
passed away so suddenly,

712
00:54:40,640 --> 00:54:41,740
and now my mom, too.

713
00:54:44,610 --> 00:54:46,420
Does your head hurt?
Should I get you something for it?

714
00:54:46,420 --> 00:54:47,520
No, I have some.

715
00:54:48,120 --> 00:54:50,620
I'm not in a good state,
so if I'm not around much...

716
00:54:52,760 --> 00:54:54,990
I understand. Take your time to heal.

717
00:54:57,090 --> 00:54:58,360
Yong Joong stopped by, didn't he?

718
00:54:59,600 --> 00:55:01,260
Are you that close? Are you dating?

719
00:55:03,570 --> 00:55:07,270
He's an old friend from the orphanage.
We were best friends in high school.

720
00:55:07,900 --> 00:55:09,740
I've told you this before.

721
00:55:14,110 --> 00:55:15,980
My brain is completely fried.

722
00:55:17,110 --> 00:55:18,610
I even forget to eat.

723
00:55:31,190 --> 00:55:33,900
To be honest,
her condition was critical at first.

724
00:55:34,060 --> 00:55:37,030
She only recovered because Director Shin
kept her on hyperbaric oxygen therapy.

725
00:55:37,430 --> 00:55:38,530
How bad was it?

726
00:55:38,740 --> 00:55:41,300
I never saw her myself.
I heard it from one of the executives.

727
00:55:42,070 --> 00:55:43,440
Is she really going to retire?

728
00:55:44,240 --> 00:55:47,580
Yes.
Has Director Choi told you differently?

729
00:55:48,540 --> 00:55:49,550
(Ha Yong Joong: "Lost Knights" Creator)

730
00:55:49,610 --> 00:55:51,450
(Actress Momo Suddenly Retires.
Agency Respects Her Wishes.)

731
00:55:51,550 --> 00:55:53,020
Looks like Geum Ba Ra
landed another scoop.

732
00:55:53,480 --> 00:55:55,620
- What is it?
- Momo announced her retirement.

733
00:55:55,950 --> 00:55:56,950
My gosh!

734
00:55:57,450 --> 00:56:00,160
(Actress Momo, 26, suddenly announced
her retirement from acting this afternoon)

735
00:56:00,220 --> 00:56:03,290
(Nua General Hospital)

736
00:56:03,360 --> 00:56:05,530
(Nua General Hospital)

737
00:56:05,600 --> 00:56:06,700
(Neurosurgery)

738
00:56:14,840 --> 00:56:18,670
Could you please give this
to Director Shin?

739
00:56:34,320 --> 00:56:35,530
Do you like the painting?

740
00:56:37,690 --> 00:56:39,160
It's a Paul Kim, isn't it?

741
00:56:43,730 --> 00:56:44,900
Take that painting down.

742
00:56:45,840 --> 00:56:47,800
- Why? It's a nice piece.
- I'm giving it to Reporter Geum.

743
00:56:51,870 --> 00:56:52,880
Hey.

744
00:56:55,040 --> 00:56:56,550
You don't have feelings for Ba Ra, do you?

745
00:57:01,720 --> 00:57:04,020
- You do?
- I've thought about it.

746
00:57:04,820 --> 00:57:06,660
You know I have a thing for smart women.

747
00:57:07,120 --> 00:57:08,190
Are you crazy?

748
00:57:08,760 --> 00:57:11,090
Are you out of your mind? You're 50!

749
00:57:11,190 --> 00:57:12,330
So what if I'm 50?

750
00:57:12,460 --> 00:57:14,260
Age is just a number.

751
00:57:14,260 --> 00:57:15,300
It's a very important number.

752
00:57:15,360 --> 00:57:17,930
People think I'm in my late thirties.

753
00:57:18,770 --> 00:57:19,970
You believe that flattery?

754
00:57:19,970 --> 00:57:22,240
In ten years, you'll be 60.

755
00:57:22,310 --> 00:57:24,240
- And Ba Ra's in her 30s.
- Her late 30s.

756
00:57:24,970 --> 00:57:27,780
Snap out of it.
She's not the right person for you.

757
00:57:27,880 --> 00:57:29,110
Don't you even think about it.

758
00:57:30,810 --> 00:57:32,480
There are plenty of other smart women
out there.

759
00:57:32,950 --> 00:57:35,590
Professor Lee Jin Hee, Dr. Shin...
Didn't you say they were both interested?

760
00:57:35,650 --> 00:57:37,020
But I'm the one who has to be attracted.

761
00:57:37,890 --> 00:57:39,420
That's greedy.

762
00:57:39,420 --> 00:57:41,090
How could you go for Ba Ra?
She could be your daughter.

763
00:57:41,260 --> 00:57:43,330
Look at actors in Hollywood.
It's the new trend.

764
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:46,660
Find a better trend to follow.
You're no Hollywood star.

765
00:57:46,730 --> 00:57:47,930
Hey, I'm quite the catch.

766
00:57:48,530 --> 00:57:51,300
James of Lim Company.
Everyone in the industry knows who I am.

767
00:57:51,670 --> 00:57:53,940
Please stop. Don't embarrass yourself.

768
00:57:54,200 --> 00:57:56,010
Fortune favors the bold.

769
00:57:56,070 --> 00:57:57,640
- James.
- You just don't want to have...

770
00:57:57,640 --> 00:57:59,210
to call her your sister-in-law, do you?

771
00:57:59,810 --> 00:58:01,040
You've really got a problem.

772
00:58:01,610 --> 00:58:04,880
That's rich. You fell head over heels
for your best friend's fiancee.

773
00:58:04,950 --> 00:58:05,980
It's not like I knew who she was!

774
00:58:06,650 --> 00:58:08,650
Either way, don't drag me into this mess.

775
00:58:10,790 --> 00:58:14,720
How'd you feel if a woman 23 years older
than you threw herself at you?

776
00:58:14,790 --> 00:58:16,190
It's different for men and women.

777
00:58:16,960 --> 00:58:18,590
You'll get torn to shreds if you do that.

778
00:58:23,000 --> 00:58:25,400
I don't care if they drag me
through the mud.

779
00:58:28,400 --> 00:58:31,510
(True correction, bright future)

780
00:58:51,730 --> 00:58:54,700
Before my mom passed away,

781
00:58:54,800 --> 00:58:57,070
she told me I had an older sister.

782
00:58:57,970 --> 00:58:59,100
It was like a deathbed confession.

783
00:59:01,270 --> 00:59:03,340
Back when you two were in high school.

784
00:59:06,910 --> 00:59:08,410
So you haven't found her yet?

785
00:59:11,580 --> 00:59:12,780
It's not that simple.

786
00:59:14,480 --> 00:59:15,550
In any case,

787
00:59:16,750 --> 00:59:19,190
I've never met her,
but you're my sister's father,

788
00:59:20,020 --> 00:59:21,520
and you used to be my mom's boyfriend.

789
00:59:22,790 --> 00:59:24,030
You don't have to be so formal with me.

790
00:59:28,100 --> 00:59:29,170
Did that...

791
00:59:30,030 --> 00:59:31,570
cause any conflict?

792
00:59:32,400 --> 00:59:33,400
No.

793
00:59:33,800 --> 00:59:36,210
It's not my place
to say anything about the past.

794
00:59:37,040 --> 00:59:38,270
I admit I was surprised.

795
00:59:39,540 --> 00:59:41,840
My father was much older than she was,

796
00:59:41,980 --> 00:59:44,380
so I had a vague inkling...

797
00:59:44,680 --> 00:59:45,950
that there was a backstory.

798
00:59:48,850 --> 00:59:50,720
If by some miracle we find her,

799
00:59:51,750 --> 00:59:56,260
I'd like to get along as sisters,
not just because my mom wanted us to.

800
00:59:56,790 --> 00:59:59,660
She's my only blood relative, after all.

801
01:00:01,130 --> 01:00:02,130
So please, let me know.

802
01:00:07,940 --> 01:00:09,040
You don't have to see me out.

803
01:00:32,460 --> 01:00:34,000
(Investigator Park)

804
01:00:42,840 --> 01:00:43,840
Hello?

805
01:00:44,810 --> 01:00:46,240
I believe we've found your daughter.

806
01:00:48,910 --> 01:00:49,910
Really?

807
01:01:15,470 --> 01:01:18,270
(Doctor Shin)

808
01:01:18,540 --> 01:01:19,540
Ladies first.

809
01:01:19,940 --> 01:01:21,410
This is our first day as a couple.

810
01:01:21,710 --> 01:01:23,510
- This is a bit of a weak celebration.
- It's more than enough.

811
01:01:23,580 --> 01:01:24,580
So I'm your number one?

812
01:01:25,350 --> 01:01:28,050
Don't tell me it's that Kim Jin Ju.

813
01:01:28,620 --> 01:01:31,050
- You're friends with Geum Ba Ra?
- Yes.

814
01:01:31,050 --> 01:01:32,390
Are both of you still single?

815
01:01:32,690 --> 01:01:34,660
- A boyfriend.
- Right.

816
01:01:34,720 --> 01:01:38,090
What if I only had eyes
for Director Shin Ju Shin?

817
01:01:38,160 --> 01:01:40,760
Shin Ju Shin is someone
women would fall for.

818
01:01:40,830 --> 01:01:43,770
- He's got it all.
- Hello, sir.

819
01:01:43,830 --> 01:01:45,230
You should brace yourself.

820
01:01:45,230 --> 01:01:46,240
Can I see her today?

821
01:01:46,300 --> 01:01:48,340
Is it because I'm thinking
about Momo too much?

822
01:01:48,970 --> 01:01:49,970
Sir.

823
01:01:51,640 --> 01:01:55,340
I just wish I had someone
I could give my all to.

824
01:01:55,580 --> 01:01:57,480
<i>I gave you my heart</i>

825
01:01:58,650 --> 01:02:00,920
<i>I gave you my tears</i>

826
01:02:01,480 --> 01:02:04,150
<i>And I gave you my dreams</i>
